The paper deals with distributed programming in functional frameworks like MapReduce, Spark, and Thrill, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also discusses program transformations, which are a common topic in Programming Languages (cs.PL). The use of algorithms and data structures in distributed programming suggests that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper discusses the verification of correctness, which is a common topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a novel verification approach, which could also fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
